      • deploy

        public LibraryItem.DeployInvocation deploy(java.lang.String ovfLibraryItemId,
                                           LibraryItemTypes.DeploymentTarget target,
                                           LibraryItemTypes.ResourcePoolDeploymentSpec deploymentSpec)
        Description copied from interface: LibraryItem
        Deploys an OVF package stored in content library to a newly created virtual machine or virtual appliance.

        This method deploys an OVF package which is stored in the library item specified by ovfLibraryItemId. It uses the deployment specification in deploymentSpec to deploy the OVF package to the location specified by target.

        Invocation Result:
        Information about the success or failure of the method, along with the details of the result or failure.

        Specified by:
        deploy in interface LibraryItem
        Parameters:
        ovfLibraryItemId - Identifier of the content library item containing the OVF package to be deployed. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.content.library.Item.
        target - Specification of the deployment target.
        deploymentSpec - Specification of how the OVF package should be deployed to the target.
        Returns:
        instance of LibraryItem.DeployInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described deploy operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.

      • filter

        public LibraryItem.FilterInvocation filter(java.lang.String ovfLibraryItemId,
                                           LibraryItemTypes.DeploymentTarget target)
        Description copied from interface: LibraryItem
        Queries an OVF package stored in content library to retrieve information to use when deploying the package. See LibraryItem.deploy(java.lang.String, com.vmware.vcenter.ovf.LibraryItemTypes.DeploymentTarget, com.vmware.vcenter.ovf.LibraryItemTypes.ResourcePoolDeploymentSpec).

        This method retrieves information from the descriptor of the OVF package stored in the library item specified by ovfLibraryItemId. The information returned by the method can be used to populate the deployment specification (see LibraryItemTypes.ResourcePoolDeploymentSpec when deploying the OVF package to the deployment target specified by target.

        Invocation Result:
        Information that can be used to populate the deployment specification (see LibraryItemTypes.ResourcePoolDeploymentSpec) when deploying the OVF package to the deployment target specified by target.

        Specified by:
        filter in interface LibraryItem
        Parameters:
        ovfLibraryItemId - Identifier of the content library item containing the OVF package to query. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.content.library.Item.
        target - Specification of the deployment target.
        Returns:
        instance of LibraryItem.FilterInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described filter operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.

      • create

        public LibraryItem.CreateInvocation create(LibraryItemTypes.DeployableIdentity source,
                                           LibraryItemTypes.CreateTarget target,
                                           LibraryItemTypes.CreateSpec createSpec)
        Description copied from interface: LibraryItem
        Creates a library item in content library from a virtual machine or virtual appliance.

        This method creates a library item in content library whose content is an OVF package derived from a source virtual machine or virtual appliance, using the supplied create specification. The OVF package may be stored as in a newly created library item or in an in an existing library item. For an existing library item whose content is updated by this method, the original content is overwritten. Meta data such as name and description is not updated for the exisitng library item.

        Invocation Result:
        Information about the success or failure of the method, along with the details of the result or failure.

        Specified by:
        create in interface LibraryItem
        Parameters:
        source - Identifier of the virtual machine or virtual appliance to use as the source.
        target - Specification of the target content library and library item.
        createSpec - Information used to create the OVF package from the source virtual machine or virtual appliance.
        Returns:
        instance of LibraryItem.CreateInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described create operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
